Problem: First n primes
Language: typescript

Statement:
Return an array of the first n prime numbers, in ascending order, where n is a non-negative integer.

Submission:
```
export function solve(n: number): number[] {
  const primes: number[] = [];
  for (let i = 2; primes.length < n - 1; i++) {
    if (primes.every((p) => i % p !== 0)) primes.push(i);
  }
  return primes;
}
```

